<br>
MCL1<br>
Aug Dex 2<br>
MoPain 2<br>
Toughness<br>
Aug Con 1<br>
LW1<br>
<br>
Unbuffed I have 1196hp, I have CON capped and have a good deal from +hit items... I do fairly well in RvR, even though my resists are the crap <br>
<br>
At any rate, I'd like to get IP, but that's a ways down the road for me... my current setup helps me with leveling mostly, but I don't have Purge or FA/FA2. I don't plan on getting purge, probably going to go with AoM to reduce the effectiveness of mez-root. So...<br>
<br>
At the rate I'm going, I should hit RR3 in the next couple of weeks, but I'll need at least 3L3 just to have enough points for FA-IP, and that leaves me with virtually nothing in the way of any other RAs... how did most of you spec your RAs as you climbed the ladder so to speak? <p></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub36.ezboard.com/bteamskald.showUserPublicProfile?gid=lxaell>l Xael l</A> at: 1/6/03 12:13:41 pm<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#d1c2a2><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub36.ezboard.com/bteamskald.showUserPublicProfile?gid=albron>Albron</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Team Skald Contributor</span><br>  Posts: 73<br> <font color=#ff0000>(1/6/03 12:27 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub36.ezboard.com/fteamskaldfrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=444.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://www.tyrantsonline.com/albron.gif WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: RA Question...</span><hr size=1> Nice setup to begin.<br>
<br>
When I was pre-50 I had very similar RAs.  They gave me some help in RvR but was mostly helpful in my PvE career.  <br>
<br>
I hit 50 before R3L3.  When i got enough points for IP I respeced and got it b/c I no longer needed the PvE RAs; MCL is really not necessary as you can but pow totems and it was &quot;nerfed&quot; (so I junked it).<br>
<br>
Some people will disagree but I find IP is a must have ASAP.  It is a life saver.  It has helped me survive when I shoulda died and therefore I got more rps.  With these extra rps (b/c I didnt die) I am able to buy new RAs.  Also at the exorbitant cost of 34 points you wanna get it ASAP b/c the points get alot harder to acquire as you grow in RRs.  Lastly IP keeps me up long enough to finish off multiple casters as my allies are killing other enemies.<br>
<br>
Now Purge is a big one to but not as important, IMHO, as IP.  The only reason i say this is b/c there are SO MANY forms of CC via root, snare, stun, mezz with many on different timers.  You'll purge a stun only to be immediately mezzed or rooted.  Its just not gonna changed the course of a fight as much as IP.<br>
 <p>Albron<br>
Level 50 Norse Skald<br>
HOOKED on speed!<br>
</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#efe0c0><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub36.ezboard.com/bteamskald.showUserPublicProfile?gid=kilgour@teamskald>Kilgour</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Team Skald Contributor</span><br>  Posts: 87<br> <font color=#ff0000>(1/6/03 5:48 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub36.ezboard.com/fteamskaldfrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=444.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> ra's</span><hr size=1> I found an interesting strat with purge.  I noticed (as i was rooted one night) that the 5 seconds it took me to relocate my purge on the quick bars, that all the casters had casted their roots, mezzes, stuns in the time i was halted.  Then i purged, killed 1 and was zerged by the rest of the enemy group.  The point here is that they tend to cast all their spells overlapping.  Give your self a breather til purge, then shoot it off.<br>
<br>
I like purge, and very much want IP.  Saving my meager points for it as I crawl past RR3 and beyond. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#d1c2a2><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub36.ezboard.com/bteamskald.showUserPublicProfile?gid=maximumstorage>MaximumStorage</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Team Skald Contributor</span><br>  Posts: 54<br> <font color=#ff0000>(1/7/03 1:44 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub36.ezboard.com/fteamskaldfrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=444.topic&index=3>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: ra's</span><hr size=1> MCL is still worth it...in a 1v1 u might be able to get it off with mezz..<br>
<br>
I dont know how many times I have been in long rvr fights where we win but barely win and while we are resting another 10 albs or hibs will rush up on us who couldnt arrive in time to save their dead realm mates...and I use my MCL so I have enuff power to mezz one and continue the fight not OOP.<br>
<br>
I have about 60k BP's and I have never bought a potion. I am hoping someday they make BP's worth something besides sad potions.<br>
<br>
Purge is ok but purging a buffed infs dragonfang doesnt mean anything, a buffed inf will kill you always. If u lucky purge might let you escape.<br>
<br>
Mastery of Pain isnt very good for 2handed users since they nerfed crits...you will see alot of you hit for 400 dmg and critical for additoin 50 dmg...very rarely any 200 dmg+ criticals in rvr. But its still the best non IP skill to buy so may as well get a few levels in it.<br>
<br>
You want to maximize your IP usage so a couple levels in toughness and aug con will give you another 125 hit points or so.<br>
<br>
Mastery of parry works really well in pve..occassionally works in rvr, more noticable than w/o any +parry..i parried a shield slam tonight <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
